-- Indonesia's Bank Rakyat shares rise 5 pct on 2013 profit jump
-- By Andjarsari Paramaditha
-- Wed Jan 22, 2014 10:21PM EST
-- None



JAKARTA, Jan 23 (Reuters) - Shares in Indonesian state-controlled lender Bank Rakyat Indonesia <BBRI.JK> jumped as much as 5.4 percent in heavy trading on Thursday after it said strong loan growth helped its 2013 profit climb 14 percent, beating estimates.

Bank Rakyat said on Wednesday afternoon that net profit for the year was 21.35 trillion rupiah ($1.8 billion), up from 18.7 trillion rupiah in 2012. The bank said that was 6.3 percent above a consensus of analysts' estimates. [ID:nL3N0KQ302]  With loans up 24 percent from a year earlier, the bank also said it has set aside 3 trillion rupiah for potential acquisitions.  At 0238 GMT, Bank Rakyat's stock was up 4.17 percent at 8,750 rupiah, leading the Jakarta exchange by volume of shares traded. The broader exchange <.JKSE> was up 0.43 percent, with the sub-index measuring banking sector shares <.JKFINA> up 1.28 percent.  The strong showing prompted some local analysts to upgrade their view of Bank Rakyat's prospects. Bahana Securities raised its target price on the shares to 9,600 rupiah, maintaining its 'buy' recommendation.